Barry Hawthorne - non-executive Director
Barry is a recipient of the prestigious Draper Medal from the Geological Society of South Africa in recognition of his significant contribution to the scientific understanding of kimberlites and the Upper Mantle processes which allow these rocks to transport diamonds to the Earth's surface.  He retired from the position of Deputy Technical Director of the Anglo American/De Beers Group after more than 40 years with the organisation, where he championed an enduring partnership between industry and academia which allowed the translation of scientific research into cutting-edge exploration methodologies.  Apart from his scientific and management expertise, Barry brings an unparalleled network of worldwide connections to assist with the Savannah's technical endeavours.
